node.text: Today, we honor the brave humanitarian workers who risk their lives to provide aid and protection. 💪

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by WFP | World Food Programme in Zambia. May be an image of 1 person, standing, tree, outdoors and text that says 'WFP'.

node.text:
❝I saw the excitement when refugees cooked foods they had not had in a long time.❞

👋 Meet Elvis, our colleague in #Zambia. Elvis has been working with WFP since October 2018 in Nchelenge District, home to a settlement that hosts over 17,200 refugees from the Democratic Republic of the Congo.

🌾He is responsible for the overall refugee operation providing food assistance to the refugees.

❝The most exciting part of my job was when we transitioned from the provision of food to cash assistance. We saw a lot of happy faces. It provided the refugees with a choice on the type of food they can buy and the dignity to buy their own food.❞ 

💵Cash assistance contributes towards diversifying diets, stimulates local economy and markets and empowers recipients to choose the food they consume. 

#WorldHumanitarianDay #WHD #WorldFoodProgramme #WFPvoices

node.text:
#Fact: Children in school today will be adults in 2030. ✨Youth are our future ✨

WFP school feeding programmes are transforming education in order to give youth everywhere endless opportunities. In 2020, 15 million schoolchildren around the world received nutritious meals and snacks from WFP.

📸 WFP / Mehedi Rahman 

#YouthDay #SchoolMeals #Education

node.text:
Regram: @antonioguterres 

The @ipcc  climate report is a code red for humanity.

The evidence is irrefutable: greenhouse gas emissions are choking our planet & placing billions of people in danger.

Global heating is affecting every region on Earth, with many of the changes becoming irreversible.

The internationally agreed threshold of 1.5°C global warming is perilously close.

We must step up our efforts and act urgently & decisively to keep the 1.5°C target alive.

#ClimateAction #ActNow

There are over 185 million indigenous women in the 🌍 Their knowledge can help feed the planet.

Indigenous people are holders of traditional knowledge, custodians of seeds, and protectors of biodiversity. But due to their dependence upon the environment, #IndigenousPeoples are among the first to face the direct consequences of #ClimateChange, such as food insecurity.

💚 Double-tap for indigenous people around the globe! 💚

#Indigenous #IndigenousDay

node.text:
❝I was amazed when WFP set up the greenhouse at my school. I learned a lot of new techniques & I've been looking for ways to replicate them at home. Finally, I built my own greenhouse.❞ 

In #Zambia, Daniel shows his little sister his #hydroponics garden. 
Daniel is a student at a secondary school in Kitwe, Zambia, where WFP has helped set up a hydroponics garden to diversify and improve school meals. 

Daniel received training in the hydroponics technology and he is responsible for looking after the site with his classmates. He was inspired to try hydroponics at home, and set up his own site using recycled tires, wood, plastic and an old mosquito net.

He likes hydroponic vegetables as he says they are tastier and more nutritious than vegetables grown in traditional gardens.

What do you think about this innovative soilless cultivation technique? 💚🥬🌱

📷 WFP / Andy Higgins

#zerohunger #wfp #worldfoodprogramme

node.text:
High tides have become a serious threat to coastal regions in Bangladesh ever since Hurricane Sidr in 2006 🌀

High tides are no longer restricted to cyclones anymore. Tides during new or full moon can reach between 8 to 12 feet, causing a long-term impact on soil, water, environment and public health of the regions. 

Today, we have the technology, science and know-how, to create more robust food systems that can withstand weather shocks and the effects of pandemics.

It's time for global commitment to reshape #FoodSystems.

🔁 Speak up 🔁

#Bangladesh #wfp #worldfoodprogramme #zerohunger

📸 WFP / Sayed Asif Mahmud

node.text:
👋 Houleye is a 19-year-old bright young woman from a small village in Mauritania, in the arid Sahel region.

📸 She took her very first photo during the WFP Storytellers vocational training on digital skills and unveiled an untapped talent. 

🔥 The very first shot she took captured a woman setting up the fire to prepare lunch for school children.

🤝 When she saw it for the first time she was incredibly happy and proud to have taken such an authentic and emblematic photo of her community.

Houleye is one of the 20 women who took part in the WFP Storytellers project in Mauritania. The training helped them portray through pictures how building resilience and strengthening resistance to shocks have changed their village 💚

Head to the link in our bio to discover the photo she took and meet the other talented women who graduated the course! 📲

#Mauritania #femalepower #womenempowerment #resilience #femalevoices

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by WFP | World Food Programme in Zambia. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Growing crops in school 💚🥬📗

This is Purity, a 12-year-old primary school student in Zambia.

Purity loves vegetables and enjoys spending time in the school garden, where she's been learning about hydroponics💦

➡️Hydroponics is a fast, soilless cultivation technique that enables plant growth all year round.

This garden has helped 200 students diversify and improve their school meals!

In Zambia, weather shocks can disrupt food systems - the production, distribution and consumption of food.

➡️Weather shocks slow down food production, causing prices to soar. This makes it more difficult for schools to buy nutritious food for students

💬''Before the hydroponics garden, we would only eat beans and maize. Now we have greens and eggplant!'' 💚🍆

📸 WFP / Andy Higgins

#wfp #worldfoodprogramme #climate #ecolifestyle #hydroponics #sustainability

🔹Increased poverty

School meals can transform communities and serve as platforms for improving #education and #foodsystems globally 🌱💙

WFP supports the creation of sustainable national school meals programmes that are nutritious, integrated and connected to local purchase. 
#UNFSS2021 #schoolmeals #zerohunger 

📷 WFP / Nick Sells
